Estimate £300 to £400.}
\end{marginfigure}

The matter was taken up by the
Secretary of State and the Government made a searching enquiry into the matter. It was
disclosed that the writer was a lad temporarily employed at the Post Office, who had
neither access to the Post Office nor Commissioners' stock, and could not have obtained
any through this source. It was further ascertained that they were purchased across the
counter in the ordinary way. The Government demanded their return but only succeeded
in recovering 23 copies of the double overprint and 4 normally overprinted stamps (presumably
se-tenant with the double overprint) and these were destroyed in the presence of
the Commissioners on the 28th August, 1899. 

