The procedure adopted for the overprinting is given as follows:—

\begin{blockquote}
"The quantity of sheets to be surcharged were sent to the printers from the Commissioners'
office in charge of an Official of that department. On the overprint being applied
they were returned to that office and carefully examined by the Stamp Commissioners
before being forwarded to the Postmaster-General, and those that showed marked errors
were withheld. These amounted to 300 and were destroyed, on the 19th September, in
the presence of four officers of the department. Yet in the large quantity of stamps handled some misprints escaped notice."
\end{blockquote}

The settings of the overprints on these stamps were consistently settings of sixty subjects.

