The error GENTS occurred on No. 53 of the sheet of the 2 on l0c., and the other recognised
variety which shows CENTS without the period comes on No. 53 on the sheet of all these
overprinted stamps. It is believed that these errors were corrected.
A number of less prominent varieties of the overprint can be found. The examination
of a sheet of the 2c. on 15c. shows the following.


Row 1—No. 2. First T short. No. 3—Second T dwarfed in many sheets.

„ 3—No. 2. Leg of W broken.

„ 4—No. 2. First dwarfed T, leg of W broken, E of different font.
No. 5. First T raised, E of different font.

„ 5—No. 1. Comma after second T.

No. 2. Dwarfed T first, W leg broken, Bar between O and C.

No. 4. Top of T broken second T.

No. 6. Last E lower leg slants.

„ 6—No. 2. First T dwarfed, E has bottom end cut.

„ 8—No. 2. First T dwarfed.

„ 9—No. 3. No stop.

In a subsequent printing we find many of these defects, etc., corrected, e.g. on Row 5,
No. 1, the comma after T has disappeared.

